# DeCoupled-AI Binary Format Specification (.brain)

Version: {{version}}

The `.brain` format is a high-performance, zero-copy binary container designed for storing quantized tensors and model weights for the DeCoupled-AI engine.

## Header Layout

| Offset | Length | Description | Value |
|--------|--------|-------------|-------|
| 0      | 8      | Magic Bytes | `BRAIN.1\0` |
| 8      | 8      | Version     | `1` |
| 16     | 8      | Manifest Len| JSON manifest length (u64) |

## JSON Manifest

Following the header is a UTF-8 JSON manifest containing model metadata:
- Model architecture (Llama, Mistral, etc.)
- Vocabulary size
- Context length
- Hyperparameters

## Tensor Index Map

Immediately following the manifest is the Tensor Index Map. Each entry is exactly **64 bytes** (packed repr C).

| Field | Size | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| name_offset | u32 | Offset to name in string table |
| name_length | u32 | Length of tensor name |
| offset | u64 | Absolute offset to tensor data |
| size_bytes | u64 | Total size in bytes |
| ndim | u32 | Number of dimensions |
| dtype | u32 | Data type enum |
| quant_type | u32 | Quantization scheme enum |
| shape | u64[8]| Tensor dimensions |

## Quantization Schemes

DeCoupled-AI supports several quantization schemes optimized for SIMD and GPU hardware:

- **F32 / F16**: Standard floating point.
- **Q4_K_M**: 4-bit quantization with 256-element blocks and 6-bit scales.
- **Q8_0**: 8-bit quantization with 32-element blocks.

## Memory Alignment

All tensor data is aligned to **64-byte** boundaries to facilitate AVX-512 and Metal/CUDA memory access.

